        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "What I can do next (within SRD‑46):\n- Run a keyword/class execution search for protein terms and common abbreviations (transferrin/apotransferrin, HSA/BSA, lactoferrin, metallothionein, ferritin) and, for transferrin, explicitly target carbonate/bicarbonate co‑ligand mentions (relevant for Tf–Fe(III) binding at physiological pH). If any vlm_* entries are found, I’ll attach their literature sources.\n- If SRD‑46 truly lacks protein constants, I can assemble a targeted comparison set of model ligands that mimic protein binding sites:\n  - Histidine/imidazole (His coordination to Cu(II)/Zn(II)),\n  - Cysteine/thiolate and glutathione (thiolates for Zn(II), Cu(I/II), Cd(II)),\n  - Carboxylates (aspartate/glutamate) and small peptides (e.g., Gly‑Gly‑His),\n  - Synergistic anions and chelators pertinent to transferrin chemistry (carbonate, citrate) and benchmarks (NTA, EDTA, DTPA).\n  I’ll report their stability constants under matched temperature/ionic strength for the metals of interest.",
